    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)
        System - Installation - EGR Tube Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>EGR Tube Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f144" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK17/K17003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR tube assembly - intake side</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 nut (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">U-bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 nut (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR valve manifold assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust tube gasket</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new exhaust tube gasket on the EGR valve manifold studs and install EGR tube
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f140" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK17/K17020.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR tube assembly - exhaust side</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 30 stud bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 26 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust tube gasket</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new exhaust tube gasket, M8 x 30 stud bolt, and two M8 x 26 bolts connecting the
                EGR tube assembly to the exhaust side EGR cooler outlet.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three M8 nuts securing the EGR tube to the EGR valve manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install threaded ends of U-bolt over the EGR tube and into the support bracket. Install two
                M8 nuts onto the U-bolt ends and finger tighten nuts to equal positions.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lightly tighten all EGR tube nuts and bolts while ensuring flanges are properly aligned.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten M8 x 30 stud bolt and two M8 x 26 bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten three M8 nuts securing the EGR tube to the EGR valve manifold to standard torque.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not crush EGR tube when torquing U-bolt M8 nuts.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Evenly tighten two M8 nuts securing the U-bolt on the support bracket to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_140.xml" xrefid="t335000502">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000502"/>. Do not crush EGR tube when torquing nuts.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
